I mention this in our chat, but here is the hourly QA checker that flags the team when we do have discrepncy in our bidstream data on Redshift.
The script does the following:

[Step 1: Environmental Setup]
-->
[Step 2: Loop Over Target Date Window (T-1)] #Note that in the past I used to do this for a 3 day lookback, but because infra got the sync more stable, 1 day is all we need now. 
-->
[Step 3: Extract & Aggregate Raw Bidstream Logs from 4 Redshift Clusters]
-->
[Step 4: Iterate Advertisers & Fetch Aggregated Metrics from TiDB]
-->
[Step 5: Apply SKAdNetwork (SKAN) Deduplication Adjustments]
-->
[Step 6: Compute Absolute & Percentage Variances for All Core Metrics]
-->
[Step 7: Evaluate Automation Flags (> 0.5% Discrepancy Threshold)] # We are poised to up this threshold to 0.1% by End of Q3 as we transition from Redshift to Iceberg.
-->
[Step 8: Push Incidents to Slack (If Any) & Upsert Full Audit Log to Snowflake]

Now, this script is automated on kestra and part 2 of the kestra flow is a seprate script that looks at the Audit log and evaluates whether it is P1,P2,P3 and a templatized email is sent to the appropriate shareholders (Data team, Engineering team, Leadership,...)